    {
      "actionDate": "2025-04-03",
      "actionDesc": "Introduced in House",
      "text": "<p><strong>Parental Rights Over The Education and Care of Their Kids Act or the PROTECT Kids Act</strong></p><p>This bill requires public elementary and middle schools, as a condition of receiving certain federal funds for elementary and secondary education, to obtain parental consent before changing a student's gender on school forms or changing a student's sex-based accommodations.</p><p>Specifically, an elementary school or a school consisting of only grades 5-8 must obtain parental consent before changing a minor student's (1) gender markers, pronouns, or preferred name on any school form; or (2) sex-based accommodations, including locker rooms or bathrooms.</p>",
      "updateDate": "2026-04-23T20:07:13Z",
      "versionCode": "00"
    }
  ]
